cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on writing style.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a neural model for encoding document information.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses a hierarchical neural network and attention mechanism.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper evaluates the model in the domain of authorship attribution, which is a subfield of information retrieval.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as authorship attribution can also be used in forensic analysis and security applications.
